Core architecture and components

- Class PalindromeGUI (in gui_app.py)
  - Purpose: Graphical user interface built with tkinter. Handles file selection, option controls, running the analysis, displaying results, highlighting text, and exporting results.

- Dataclass DetectionOptions (in palindrome_detector.py)
  - Purpose: Encapsulates detection settings (min length, ignore case/non-alnum, which categories to search).

- Dataclass PalindromeMatch (in palindrome_detector.py)
  - Purpose: Represents a single palindrome detection result with category, text, normalized text, length, line number, start/end columns, etc.

- Class IndexMapper (in palindrome_detector.py)
  - Purpose: Maps global character offsets in the loaded text to (line number, column) for accurate highlighting and result reporting.

- Function normalize_text(text, ignore_case, ignore_non_alnum) (in palindrome_detector.py)
  - Purpose: Normalize a string according to options for palindrome checking.

- Function is_palindrome(text, ignore_case, ignore_non_alnum) (in palindrome_detector.py)
  - Purpose: Determine if a string is a palindrome under the chosen options.

- Function find_palindromic_words(text, min_length, ignore_case, ignore_non_alnum) (in palindrome_detector.py)
  - Purpose: Scan the entire text for palindromic words and return a list of PalindromeMatch objects.

- Function find_palindromic_lines(text, min_length, ignore_case, ignore_non_alnum) (in palindrome_detector.py)
  - Purpose: Check each line (excluding line breaks) to see if the whole line is a palindrome.

- Function find_palindromic_sentences(text, min_length, ignore_case, ignore_non_alnum) (in palindrome_detector.py)
  - Purpose: Split text into sentence-like segments and detect palindromes at the sentence level.

- Function detect_palindromes(text, options) (in palindrome_detector.py)
  - Purpose: Orchestrates the detection pipeline according to options, returning a combined list of results.

- Function read_text_file(path) (in file_utils.py)
  - Purpose: Robustly read a text file trying common encodings and return its content as a string.

- Function export_results_to_csv(path, results) (in exporter.py)
  - Purpose: Save the detection results to a CSV file.

